Loved my sandwich! Got the big kahuna (tuna melt) and every bite was amazing.

It was good went in for a quick lunch orderd a breakfast sammie for luch 8 $ and it filled me up for a long time , you can order your lunch in advance

Next time I'll be back with my relatives.
Excellent lunch sandwiches! We're definitely going back.
Great sandwiches, if it becomes crowded, you'll wait awhile.
Love this spot both for great sandwiches and as noir lounge at night. My word is bond
Great sandwiches, good service and chill environment.

These sandwiches are so yummy! A bit of a wait but totally worth it.
Great place and vibe. They have a few vegetarian options tried the dolce Vita and was great. A slight walk from the Civic center Bart station but a good place.

This place has Legit sandwiches.  Best French bread I've had outside of New Orleans. Great flavor, never dry, always juicy. Pick one, you can't go wrong. Their potato chips are excellent, made in-house.  The space has a prohibition era …

Edible, but bland with service to match. I've tried this place a handful of times now and have always felt disappointed afterwards. The last straw was a near-30 minute wait for two sandwiches. With all of the other options in or around Hayes I'm not sure why you would stop here.
Very underrated sandwich shop. No line and an incredible sandwich. I got the “Cordon Blue” which was a special
Excellent sandwhichs very good service

Bar at night turned sandwich shop by day. The highlight here is the amazing food. The menu features a great mix of sandwiches and salads. In the morning you can also get breakfast sandwiches. I got a sandwich and side salad. The sandwich …
Love Lunchpad. The décor alone is worth going, but the sandwiches and salads are the damn good. If you are trying to figure out where to go in Hayes Valley and you haven't been here, then go here.
Awesome salads! Great place for small parties too.

Way overpriced.  Sandwich + sparkling water + chips came out to $20.  Sat and waited for my sandwich for 20 minutes before asking the bartender what's up.  It was sitting behind the bar and they forgot to call my name.  What the ____ man, i …
The sandwiches are really good, but on the pricey side. The space is quite nice, but very dark. It must also double as a bar/dinner place.

Noir Lounge by night, Lunchpad by day. I like NL so I figured I'd give this place a whirl. Their sandwiches are really good and pretty huge - I doubt you'll need a side! Only reason this isn't a 5 is that their coffee is kinda nasty - don't recommend. But all in all it's a solid lunch choice.
Great for a quick breakfast and coffee on the way to the Painted Ladies.
Decent sandwich brunch spot inside an atmospheric noir-styled bar.
Best sandwiches in sf
Meh....
The salads are delicious and HUGE!
The blt is amazing

I stumbled upon Lunchpad on a Saturday afternoon and ordered the A-Bomb sandwich (with habanero candied bacon!), a Mexican Coke, and rosemary-dusted potato chips. This was arguably the best sandwich I've had in my 2.5 years in San Francisco.

Loved the food and atmosphere.  My main complaint was that the salad I ordered came with dressing on the side and it was a rather large (& expensive salad at $13) and the dressing to salad ratio was way off and there little container of …

Had the tuna salad sandwich. The sandwich came with pickled green beans. Overall, pretty good. I would have preferred more tuna salad because I ran out of tuna and was left with only 🍞.  Chips are homemade and tasty. Next time, I will try a different sandwich.
These are probably the best sandwiches in all of SF. The turkey drizzle is really a standout, and be sure to get the house made chips!
Would have been a 5 star as the food/sandwich I had was delicious. (B.L.Whaat) The service was just a little chaotic.
Delicious sandwiches. Great service!

Delicious turkey drizzle! Homemade chips! Ice cold drinks!  Wasn't sure to go in as we were the only ones, but so glad I did. Rush hour happened just after and Launchpad is clearly appreciated by the locals and tourists (painted sisters just nearby). Would come again!
Love this place.  The turkey drizzle is awesone. Adam makes his own habenaro bacon so good.
Super cozy and it's not overcrowded like most of the other places in the area.

I'm a regular and generally picky about my food. Having had many of the sandwiches never disappointed. There is an art to making a good sandwich and Lunchpad is artistic and the combos are wonderful. Lover the bread, just the right texture …
Great food, a little dark but suitable atmosphere.

Really, really cool low-key spot with lots of seating and unique decor. We were there for a Saturday lunch, so I'm not sure if it gets crazy and packed in the evening. The sandwiches were good, good beer selection. Not too pricey. Good spot.
Great place to lunch.  Quick service.  I love the lounge feel.  There are high backed arm chairs at well spaced tables for privacy and comfort.
Awesome sandwiches!
Cozy, high quality, and inexpensive sandwiches. Great little place 😊

Absolutely wonderful and balanced sandwich. Had the Italian stallion which was a daily special. The turkey, bacon, pesto, cheddar... Oh! It was insane. The little red onion on top and some crisp veggies made this an all around great …
Awesome sandwiches!
I'm usually not a fan of bacon on my sandwich as it tends to be too salty. But the habanero candied bacon is amazing. Great sandwiches and great vibe!
Great vibe, service is good, quality products, I strongly recommend it for a relaxing lunch with friends
Got the huevos rancheros. Was OK. They were out of my top choice. All my friends got sandwiches, tried one, pretty good, nothing to write home about.
The house salad is fairly large and filling. Sandwiches are really good as well. This place tends to be my goto lunch spot in Hayes valley.
This place has the best salads and sandwiches I've ever had. Seriously. It's in charmingly eclectically decorated wine bar only during lunchtime. Very popular with the young professional crowd.

Super cute and delicious sandwich spot.  I ordered the turkey drizzle, a sandwich with roast turkey, habanero candied bacon, swiss cheese, cashew pesto, caramelized onions, giardiniera, greens, tomatoes and a drizzle of balsamic reduction. …
Bar at night, sandwich spot during the day. I ordered the tomato soup and the grilled cheese. I considered the bread too thick so the cheese got lost in the middle.

WOW! So many great things to choose from at this place. I ended up ordering A-Bomb sandwich as a salad. The habanero candied bacon is unreal and one of the most delicious things I've ever eaten. The salad was huge and full of yummy meats, …
Great, fresh sandwiches.  Come early as they sometimes run out of things. One day a week they have a fried chicken sandwich special that is amazing.

Maybe I just don't get this place. It's in a bar, but they don't serve alcohol. That is tragic. When I was there at 1:30 they ran out of bread for the folks in line after us. The sandwiches are just OK. The two we ordered were fairly bland, …
Simple menu with great, fast service! The food was yummy and very filling.

This is a cute joint, with a relaxed atmosphere, and very good (but not great) sandwiches. I would have given this 3.5 stars for the food (Ike's, near Duboce Park, sets the bar for sandwiches with five stars), but rounded up because I liked everything else about Lunchpad, including the lack of a wait on busy Hayes St on a Saturday.

Slightly pricey (what isn't these days) solid sandwiches and breakfast options. Most come with a pickle on the side, which is great. One of the women working there gave us free chocolate chip cookies the other day!
one of the best sandwiches I have had in the city!!

If you like sandwiches, then this place is for you. The best sandwich I think is their chicken lil, which is a big hearty chicken salad sandwich. It's not too drippy with mayo. On Wednesdays, they have the chicken run, which is a fried …

AN ABSOLUTE GEM. This is basically Noir Lounge at any other given time but taken over as a lunch pop-up during the week. Not that I have anything against Noir Lounge, but this place could be more different than its host.  The sandos here …
Breakfast! Perfect storm

Great food!!!
Tasty treats and a chill spot to enjoy them!
Inventive, delectable sandwiches with tasty Parmesan chips in a lovely (Noir Lounge) interior. Will be back!
